result.execSummary:
Lonnie Haggins was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Lonnie Haggins was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Lonnie Haggins not in court, defendant in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
 Court orders case closed defendant was picked up by the State of Illinois on 5.21.15.

Defendant Lonnie Haggins in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  Defendant Lonnie Haggins in custody.  
Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Pocan, Branch 26.  
Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  
Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus. 
Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of ILLINOIS.  Defendant waived extradition.  Signed Waiver of Extradition received and filed.  
Court ordered the defendant remanded into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Status conference scheduled for June 2, 2015 at 08:30 am.
